Peyvand - simple webkit-based browser
==================================
Peyvand is a fork of surf, which is a simple Web browser based on WebKit/GTK+.

Requirements
------------
In order to build Peyvand you need GTK+ and Webkit/GTK+ header files.

In order to use the functionality of the url-bar, also install dmenu[0].

Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (peyvand is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install peyvand (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install

Running peyvand
------------
run
	peyvand [URI]

See the manpage for further options.

Running peyvand in tabbed
----------------------
For running peyvand in tabbed[1] there is a script included in the distribution,
which is run like this:

	surf-open.sh [URI]

Further invocations of the script will run surf with the specified URI in this
instance of tabbed.

[0] http://tools.suckless.org/dmenu
[1] http://tools.suckless.org/tabbed
